{
  "texts": [
    "A word frequency analysis in Study 1A's reviews revealed that the word \"bacon\" appeared in 10.36% of the ChatGPT reviews but was scarcely mentioned in human expert reviews (only once as \"bacon fat\").",
    "The result suggested that content from generative AI had tendencies toward excessive use of specific terms and hallucinations.",
    "The results of Study 1B provide the other side of the story from the perspective of consumers.",
    "When reading a selection of the reviews from Study 1A, consumers found that certain reviews by human experts displayed lower levels of embodied cognition, expertise, and usefulness, potentially because human experts used more idiosyncratic structures for reviews.",
    "As in Study 1A, they noted that ChatGPT reviews contained more positive emotions."
  ]
}